And robust peer reviewed crypto not prone to failure. Most men hard systems proposed after hashcash for few years were broken in peer review
also convenient, simple to implement in any language with SHA library & even visually inspect difficulty with shasum command line tools etc.
rationale for simplicity was for low gate count & assumed smartphones, laptops would end up with silicon like 21 chip on die or coprocessor.
hashcash design assumed ASICs would come, examined & rejected mem hard, pubkey & hw footprint complexity defences in interests of simplicity
ie your hashcash v2 PoW format to be both a valid pool share & hashcash stamp.
did muse about v2 format hashcash-sha256 as merge-mineable with bitcoin. problem is ASIC is ultra-spam power vs cpu/gpu
